qualifications_preferred:
Preferred Qualifications: Preference will be given to students who engage in and have a passion for Engineering Design, as well as (1) have experience marking technical and reflective writing,  (2) have taught or assisted in design course(s), especially ESC101/102/203/204, (3) have taken ESC101, ESC102 and ESC204, (3) have been or are currently enrolled in Engineering Science, (5) have worked on design projects with global/international context, impact or significance, (6) have prior experience with (course-based or from industry) teamwork and project management, (7) have competencies in one or more of the following technical areas (including adapting to new software/tools and navigating documentation/resources within these areas): 
o system-level electrical circuit design (e.g.: for powering embedded systems; for signal conditioning; for interfacing microcontrollers, sensors, actuators, and digital input/output) 
o embedded system/microcontroller programming and interfacing including familiarity with MicroPython or CircuitPython
o computer programming for system development and/or data analysis (Python, MATLAB preferred)
o mechanical and/or mechatronic design (including CAD, casing design, and/or mechanical actuation)
o traditional fabrication methods (wood and/or metalworking)
o digital fabrication methods (3D printing and/or laser cutting and/or CNC)
o internet-of-things (IoT), (8) have competencies in multiple of the following transdisciplinary areas (including adapting to new software/tools and navigating documentation/resources):
o multi-disciplinary (engineering and non-engineering) team based design; 
o  technical communication;
o cross-cultural communication/engagement;
o project management;
